#change color scale for 5 regions
pal = list(sns.color_palette(palette='viridis', n_colors=5).as_hex())

def kde_ridge(df_input, col_name, time, title):
    sns.set_theme(style="white", rc={"axes.facecolor": (0, 0, 0, 0)})

    # Initialize the FacetGrid object
    g = sns.FacetGrid(df_input, row= time, hue=time, aspect=15, height=0.65, palette=pal)

    # Draw the densities in a few steps
    g.map(sns.kdeplot, col_name,
          bw_adjust=.5, clip_on=False,fill=True, alpha=1, linewidth=1.5)

    #g.map(sns.kdeplot, col_name, clip_on=False, color="w", lw=2, bw_adjust=.5)

    # passing color=None to refline() uses the hue mapping
    g.map(plt.axhline, y=0, linewidth=2, linestyle="-", color=None, clip_on=False)
    
    def label(x, color, label):
        ax = plt.gca()
        ax.text(0, .2, label, fontweight="bold", color=color,ha="left", va="center", transform=ax.transAxes)
    
    g.map(label, time)

    # Set the subplots to overlap
    g.fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=-.25)

    # Remove axes details that don't play well with overlap
    g.set_titles("")
    g.set(yticks=[], ylabel="", xlabel= title)
    g.despine(bottom=True, left=True)

    return g

#change color scale for 5 regions
pal = list(sns.color_palette(palette='viridis', n_colors=5).as_hex())

def line_ridge(df_input, col_name, time, title, date):

    sns.set_theme(style="white", rc={"axes.facecolor": (0, 0, 0, 0)})

    # Initialize the FacetGrid object
    g = sns.FacetGrid(df_input, row= time, hue=time, aspect=8, palette=pal)

    # sns.lineplot(x='date', y='new_confirmed', hue='region', data=df_cases_NOVO, palette='bright', legend='full')
    # Draw the densities in a few steps
    g.map(sns.lineplot, date, col_name, clip_on=False, alpha=1, linewidth=1.5)

    #g.map(sns.lineplot, col_name, clip_on=False, color="w", lw=2)

    # passing color=None to refline() uses the hue mapping
    g.map(plt.axhline, y=0, linewidth=2, linestyle="-", color="k", clip_on=False)
    
    def label(x, color, label):
        ax = plt.gca()
        ax.text(0, .2, label, fontsize="24", fontweight="bold", color=color,ha="left", va="center", transform=ax.transAxes)
    
    g.map(label, time)

    # Set the subplots to overlap
    g.fig.subplots_adjust(hspace=-.25)

    # Remove axes details that don't play well with overlap
    g.set_titles("")
    g.set(yticks=[], ylabel="", xlabel= title)
    g.despine(bottom=True, left=True)

    return g
